                {
                    "id": "high_pH_O3_dominates",
                    "description": "pH=6: sulfite (SO3\u00b2\u207b) fraction increases sharply (K_s2/H+ = 66), so the O3 term (k2=1.5e6 m\u00b3/mol/s) dominates over H2O2. Verifies R_O3 > R_H2O2 at high pH (O3 path is pH-sensitive via SO3\u00b2\u207b). S&P \u00a77.5: at pH<5 H2O2 dominates; at pH>5 O3 takes over.",
